<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747151>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Chondriovelum adeliense (Livingstone); Recent, BANZARE Station 40, 66.2°S, 49.62°E, 300 m depth, Enderby Land, Antarctica (SAM collection). (a) Bleached colony showing autozooids and avicularia. (b) Enlargement of avicularium. (c) Unbleached colony with cuticle partly intact, showing dried avicularian mandibles (e.g. arrow). Scale bars: a, c = 1 mm; b = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4747151/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

